// useSession
// Provides the full session store interface — current session, diagrams, documents, designs, collab state, and all actions.

A thin facade over the session store using shallow comparison to prevent unnecessary re-renders.
Exposes everything a component needs to read and mutate session state from one hook call.

FUNCTION useSession() -> UseSessionReturn                                       EXPORT
  CALLS: useSessionStore (sessionStore)
  Reads all session state and actions from the store using shallow comparison.
  Derives selectedDiagram, selectedDocument, and selectedDesign by calling the corresponding store getters.
  Returns the complete session interface including: currentSession, isLoading, error, diagrams,
  documents, designs, collabState, all selection IDs, and all CRUD/selection/utility actions.
